<figureCitation box="[567,719,177,202]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-1@6.[178,1138,142,1493]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Dorsal view of the female metasoma, with apex of metasoma shown to the left (a, c e) and detail of the terga 1–3 to the right (b, d, f) (midline of sclerite to the right in b, d, f). (a, b) Xylocopa bimaculata Friese, 1903, holotype; (c, d) Xylocopa fortuita sp. nov., holotype (shorter lateral pubescence compared to that of other two specimens is an artefact due to the condition in which the specimen was obtained; see text for details); (e, f) Xylocopa piligera Maidl, 1912, specimen from Serra da Bocaina, São José do Barreiro, São Paulo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4779893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4779893/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="387">Figures 3c, d</figureCitation>
